<p><strong>Beastclaw Greathammer</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Great Hammers" href="/Great+Hammers">Great Hammer (Warhammer)</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Beastclaw Greathammer</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>&nbsp;and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a>&nbsp;and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for high strength players who can hold this weapon's weight.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Greathammer with a striking end modelled to resemble five beastly claws.</em></p> 
 <p><em>The black nails protruding from golden fur are said to represent Serosh, Lord of Beasts, who went to become King Godfrey's Regent.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Beastclaw Greathammer in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Beastclaw Greathammer weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Gurranq Beast Clergyman" href="/Gurranq+Beast+Clergyman">Gurranq</a> will reward the player with this after turning in their 7th <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Deathroot" href="/Deathroot" target="">Deathroot</a>.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Beastclaw Greathammer Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Regal Beastclaw" href="/Regal+Beastclaw" target="">Regal Beastclaw</a> 
  <ul> 
   <li>"<em>Slam the hammer into the ground, rending the land asunder with the armament's five bestial claws."</em></li> 
   <li>The effect is similar to the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Beast Claw" href="/Beast+Claw" target="">Beast Claw</a> incantation that is also received from <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Gurranq Beast Clergyman" href="/Gurranq+Beast+Clergyman">Gurranq</a></li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a> and cannot be buffed with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic" href="/Magic" target="">Magic</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a></li> 
 <li><strong>Beastclaw Greathammer</strong>&nbsp;can be upgraded by using&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a>.)</li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;500</li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Moveset &amp; Videos in&nbsp;Elden Ring for&nbsp;Beastclaw Greathammer</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Videos for the Beastclaw Greathammer Coming Soon</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Beastclaw Greathammer Upgrades in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Please see the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Upgrades" href="/Upgrades" target="">Upgrades</a>&nbsp;page to understand the weapon bolstering process.</p> 
<p>Requires regular reinforcement with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></p> 
<p>This upgrade can be enchanted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic Spells" href="/Magic+Spells" target="">Magic</a>&nbsp;or boosted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</p> 
