				<li id="16726833" class="cmnt-root" data="9" data-d="1656557034000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t580170/Beastclaw-Greathammer" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">29 Jun 2022 22:43</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16726833" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">You have to have a plan for this hammer aside from just raw damage or standalone weapon art, however it is not as bad as made out to be. My biggest issue is the split damage type everything beastial is pure physical yet this hammer has holy damage.<br/><br/>In PVP I like to have a second hammer with Golden Land, and when people run from the golden land darts I flip to this weapon and throw its weapon art at them. It often catches them at a pretty decent range for decent damage, and will often clip even a little past the point where it seems like the claw projectiles disappears. Also the attack has good hyper armor so you can throw it down for a trade and if done at close range you will win that trade almost all the time. Often pvp opponents will think they can heal at a distance that is right at the tip of this weapon art&apos;s range, so often an easy way to punish healing.<br/><br/>Unlike most weapons though for this weapon to be useful you have to really think about how you are using it, otherwise you will feel underwhelmed by it. If you want weapons that require no thinking, they make those too but this isn&apos;t one of those.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16726833" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16726833" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">1</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>9</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16726833"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16726833" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16726833"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
