				<li id="16605005" class="cmnt-root" data="16" data-d="1649403891000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t580170/Beastclaw-Greathammer" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">08 Apr 2022 03:44</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16605005" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">with 45 Strength+Faith and 40 Dex, this hammer has a two-handed AR of 793 {284 base physical damage + 264 str/dex scaling physical damage + 183 base holy damage + 60 faith scaling holy damage}. A direct hit with the weapon-art is doing around 1300 damage on the NG+ omen ogre things in the capital sewers.<br/><br/>I&apos;m fielding this on my bestial character--as a secondary/backup weapon--mainly for times when the cinquedea dagger&apos;s range becomes an issue (like on horseback, or fighting erdtree avatars.) Combined with stones of gurranq incantation, I&apos;m staggering big enemies insanely quickly. Also, the weapon-art has good hyper-armor, making it difficult for enemies to interrupt.<br/><br/>Are there better/more efficient weapons for this purpose? Yeah. Could/should it be buffed? Idk maybe. But it&apos;s enough for me. It suits my needs, and more importantly the theme of my build.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16605005" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-1660500